Kardan Jumps Second Day After Plan to Repurchase Shares

-- B y   S u s a n   L e r n e r
-- 
2011-09-27T13:53:09Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-27/kardan-jumps-a-second-day-after-announcing-share-repurchase-plan.html
Kardan NV (KRNV)  advanced for a second day
after the investor in property, water infrastructure and
financial services said yesterday it will spend as much as 15
million euros ($20 million) to repurchase shares.  The stock climbed 13 percent to 9.564 shekels at the 4:30
close in  Tel Aviv , bringing the two-day increase to 25 percent,
the biggest such gain since April 2009.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Susan Lerner  in Jerusalem at 
 slerner2@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Claudia Maedler at 
 cmaedler@bloomberg.net  